</i></p><p class="sc-dFtzxp kOHCjr pf-14_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3"><span style="color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">In health and social care, understanding and adhering to RIDDOR (Reporting of Injuries, Diseases and Dangerous Occurrences Regulations) is paramount. In this blog, Dr Richard Dune aims to provide a detailed overview of RIDDOR, highlighting its significance, key definitions, relevant legislation, and best practices.</span></p></div></div></div></div></div><button type="button" style="visibility:visible" aria-label="Previous" class="pf-slider-prev none hide"></button><button type="button" style="visibility:visible" aria-label="Next" class="pf-slider-next none hide"></button></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div data-section-id="pf-4ea1" data-category="Collection Suggestion" data-name="Tea" data-pf-type="Section" class="sc-lkgTHX jrzygT pf-16_ pf-color-scheme-1"><div style="--cw:1170px" class="sc-fmBCVi iwpzju"><div class="sc-egiyK kKHsVi pf-17_ pf-r pf-c-lm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-fXEqDS hwCMhq pf-18_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-ctqQKy eJZCTA pf-19_ pf-heading-1-h3">Key facts and statistics</h3><p class="sc-dFtzxp kOHCjr pf-21_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">RIDDOR mandates reporting work-related accidents leading to serious injury, disease, or danger. According to the Health and Safety Executive (HSE), over 60,000 reported injuries were in the health and social care sector in 2023 alone, underscoring the need for stringent reporting protocols.








































































</p></div></div></div><div class="sc-egiyK kKHsVi pf-23_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-fXEqDS hwCMhq pf-24_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-ctqQKy eJZCTA pf-25_ pf-heading-1-h3">Key definitions</h3><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-cbTzjv cdRhtw pf-27_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-hjGZqJ gtgMXo pf-28_ pf-text-1"><strong>Serious injury</strong> - Any injury leading to an absence from work for more than seven days.


</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-hjGZqJ gtgMXo pf-30_ pf-text-1"><strong>Dangerous occurrence</strong> - Near misses or incidents posing significant risk.</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-hjGZqJ gtgMXo pf-32_ pf-text-1"><strong>Occupational disease</strong> - Illness directly attributed to workplace conditions.

</li></ul></div></div></div><div class="sc-egiyK kKHsVi pf-34_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-fXEqDS hwCMhq pf-35_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-ctqQKy eJZCTA pf-36_ pf-heading-1-h3">Relevant legislation and regulations</h3><p class="sc-dFtzxp kOHCjr pf-38_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3"> RIDDOR is governed by the Health and Safety at Work Act 1974 and subsequent amendments. It mandates employers, the self-employed, and responsible persons to report specified incidents to the HSE or relevant local authority.










































































